.TH "xprt_conditional_disconnect" 9 "xprt_conditional_disconnect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xprt_conditional_disconnect \- force a transport to disconnect
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xprt_conditional_disconnect
.BI "(struct rpc_xprt *xprt "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cookie "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xprt" 12
transport to disconnect
.IP "cookie" 12
'connection cookie'
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This attempts to break the connection if and only if 'cookie' matches
the current transport 'connection cookie'. It ensures that we don't
try to break the connection more than once when we need to retransmit
a batch of RPC requests.
